The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, July 28, 2004 				 Gunfight on banks of Dal Lake
 MUKHTAR AHMAD 																								Srinagar, July 27: The banks of the picturesque Dal Lake turned into a battlefield tonight with a suicide squad storming a Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF) camp located in a hotel.																								Initial reports said one militant was killed and four CRPF jawans were injured in the shootout that followed. The gun battle stretched late into the night.																								Various battalions of the CRPF have set up camp at a number of hotels on the Dal Lake to secure the area for tourists. Almost all the luxury hotels in the area are located on the banks of the lake. Hundreds of Amarnath pilgrims were in the other hotels when the attack occurred.																								Sources said a group of heavily armed fidayeen attacked the paramilitary camp in Hotel Livard with grenades and assault rifles. 																								An officer said the camp had been cordoned off by paramilitary forces who have taken position in houseboats near the hotel.																								A spokesperson for the Al-Mansoorian militant outfit phoned a local agency to claim responsibility for the attack.																								In Jammu, five special police officers were killed in a militant attack.
